meta {
  title = llms.txt,
  order = 4,
  icon = bot
}

Tiramisu Docs generates machine-readable documentation files that help AI assistants understand your docs without scraping your website.

h3 { Endpoints }

Three endpoints are automatically generated:

table {
  row = [bold { Endpoint }, bold { Description }],
  row = [code { /llms.txt }, A concise summary of your documentation structure with links to each page],
  row = [code { /llms-full.txt }, The complete content of all documentation pages in plain text],
  row = [code { /skill.md }, A Claude Code skill file that teaches Claude how to use your documentation]
}

h3 { llms.txt }

The code { /llms.txt } file follows the bold { llms.txt standard } — a lightweight format that helps AI models discover and navigate your documentation. It contains:

list {
  Your site title and description,
  A list of all documentation pages with their URLs and descriptions,
  Links to the full-text version
}

h3 { llms-full.txt }

The code { /llms-full.txt } endpoint provides the complete content of every documentation page in plain text format. This is useful for AI assistants that need to ingest your full documentation.

h3 { skill.md }

The code { /skill.md } endpoint generates a Claude Code skill file. This file can be used as a Claude Code skill to teach Claude about your documentation structure and content.

h3 { Generator Functions }

These endpoints are powered by three functions you can use in your SvelteKit routes:

codeblock { language = typescript, """import {
  generateLlmsTxt,
  generateLlmsFullTxt,
  generateSkillMd,
} from "@tiramisu-docs/kit";""" }

Each function returns a string that you can serve from a SvelteKit endpoint:

codeblock { language = typescript, """// src/routes/llms.txt/+server.ts
import { generateLlmsTxt } from "@tiramisu-docs/kit";

export const GET = async () => {
  const content = await generateLlmsTxt();
  return new Response(content, {
    headers: { "Content-Type": "text/plain" },
  });
};""" }
